=== Parliamentary QA ===
Title: Education on Vaping
Date: 11 May 2021
Document Type: Parliamentary QA (Written Answer)
Topic: Public education, health awareness, vaping, electronic nicotine delivery systems (ENDS)

Summary:
- Question: Measures to counter the perception that vaping is less harmful than smoking.
- Ministry of Health response:
  1. WHO declares ENDS harmful and not safer than cigarettes; ENDS can act as a gateway to traditional smoking.
  2. Health Promotion Board (HPB) launched a 2019 public education campaign targeting:
     - Youths aged 18â€“25  
     - Parents of teenage children  
     Campaign highlighted harmful contents of e-cigarettes.
  3. HPB works with Ministry of Education and Institutes of Higher Learning to:
     - Raise awareness on tobacco-free lifestyle benefits  
     - Encourage youths to stay vape-free  
     - Organize online learning activities, gamification methods (e.g., virtual escape rooms), self-directed resources, and educator training.
  4. General public:
     - HealthHub.sg provides information on harms of vaping  
     - Health Sciences Authority (HSA) engages media to emphasize prohibition of sale, use, possession for sale, importation, and distribution of e-vaporisers in Singapore.

Key Entities:
- Ministry of Health (MOH)  
- Health Promotion Board (HPB)  
- Health Sciences Authority (HSA)  
- World Health Organization (WHO)  
- Ministry of Education  
- Institutes of Higher Learning  

Key Concepts:
- ENDS are harmful; not safer than cigarettes  
- Vaping may act as a gateway to smoking  
- Public education through campaigns, digital tools, and educator training  
- Regulatory enforcement against possession, sale, and distribution

Author / Issuer:
Ministry of Health (MOH), Health Promotion Board (HPB), Health Sciences Authority (HSA)
Date of Issue: 11 May 2021
